my puppy pees every morning when he sees me or my husband and later when we get home does anyone knows why when he sees us he's not afraid at all he's so excited and he stays outside not inside he's a lab this is called submissive urination and indicates that the dog is an omega and very submissive this isn't a bad thing i like omega dogs as they are not aggressive towards people or other dogs this behavior is best treated by avoidance do not get the dog excited when you come home usually this will require that you ignore the dog for about minutes usually as the dog gets older it normally doesn't become all that excited when it first sees you but this will take years Housebreaking Dog Dog training Crate training Gray Wolf Episodes of Lost (Season 1) Cat Dog show Similarities between the Bible and the Qur'an Syphon Filter Human sexual behavior Hamster Shaggy dog story Poker jargon Labrador Retriever Honey and Clover Socialization Obedience training Zoophilia Theory of conduct Teacher's Pet (Disney) Futurama (TV series - season 5) Nicomachean Ethics Toilet humour Wild at Heart (Buffy episode) Traditionalist Catholic Goodness and value theory Guinea pig Rabies The Strangerhood Kim Possible Jumpstart 3rd Grade Angel One (TNG episode) Dilbert Prostate cancer Pok__mon Live! Procrastination Phonon Ranma __ characters Dog breeding Campfire Tales Beethoven (film) Traumatic incident reduction Fancy rat Piccolo Junior Saga Professional wrestling double-team maneuvers Karen Horney Maison Ikkoku German Shepherd Dog Prisoner's dilemma Mixed-breed dog Rottweiler House Mouse The Death Gate Cycle Professional wrestling match types Daria Phoebe Halliwell Harry Potter and the Prisoner of Azkaban Noam Chomsky Insulin English Springer Spaniel The Fairly OddParents Puppy mill Dobermann Professional wrestling holds Futurama (TV series - season 4) Manos: The Hands of Fate Coming of Age (TNG episode) Ron and Fez Samus Aran We'll Always Have Paris (TNG episode) Sonic the Hedgehog RLC circuit